reviews.review_text: english country garden o.k. so yes both of these gigs at this baseball field were fun and cool,i remember we were all stoked about the twelve song first set! its true the park was in a suburban neighborhood,surrounded by single family houses on like quarter acre lots,and two lane roads with on street parking.real regular stuff,good times.years later listening to the tape,something caught my ear.i may be wrong but I'm pretty sure the song,melody,music that jerry plays behind bob during 'take a step back' before Brother Esau is part of a cool little song by R.M.Jordan called English Country Garden.i had to smile because i had just discovered this song,and i like it for its cadence,and smart little lyrics.i rate the party not the recording,but i do love audience tapes
